JBomberman are a reimplementation/upgrade of the game Atomic Bomberman. The main goals will be to make the game look and feel as the original one, but add features like TCP/IP networking, support for new operating systems, and so on.


How to download and build the project:

Ubuntu/Debian
  1. Install Java6 JDK using "apt-get install sun-java6-jdk"
  2. Install Maven2 using "apt-get install maven2"
  3. Install Git using "apt-get install git-arch"
  4. Download the source using "git clone git://github.com/mattiz/JBomberman.git"
  5. Change directory to "JBomberman"
  6. Build the project using "mvn package"
  7. Change directory to "target"
  8. Run the project using "java -cp jbomberman-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar org.moogirc.jbomberman.App"

Windows
  1. Download and install Java6 JDK from http://java.sun.com
  2. Add the Java6 bin directory to system path
  3. Download and install Maven2 from http://maven.apache.org/download.html
  4. Add the Maven bin directory to system path
  5. Download and install Git using the instructions in http://github.com/guides/using-git-and-github-for-the-windows-for-newbies
  6. Download the source using "git clone git://github.com/mattiz/JBomberman.git"
  7. Change directory to "JBomberman"
  8. Build the project using "mvn package"
  9. Change directory to "target"
  10. Run the project using "java -cp jbomberman-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar org.moogirc.jbomberman.App"


How to use Eclipse for the project

  1. Install the Eclipse plug-in using the instructions in http://github.com/guides/using-the-egit-eclipse-plugin-with-github
  2. Run "mvn eclipse:eclipse" in the project directory
  3. Open the newly generated project files
